.TH "sys_sched_rr_get_interval" 9 "sys_sched_rr_get_interval" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sys_sched_rr_get_interval \- return the default timeslice of a process.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" sys_sched_rr_get_interval
.BI "(pid_t pid "  ","
.BI "struct __kernel_timespec __user * interval "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pid" 12
pid of the process.
.IP "interval" 12
userspace pointer to the timeslice value.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
this syscall writes the default timeslice value of a given process
into the user-space timespec buffer. A value of '0' means infinity.
.SH "RETURN"
On success, 0 and the timeslice is in \fIinterval\fP. Otherwise,
an error code.
